My luteal phase guide 👇(read)💯
During the luteal phase, progesterone rises, and your energy may dip. Many women with PCOS or hormonal imbalances feel more emotional, bloated, or fatigued here.

🧘‍♀️ 1. Focus on Rest + Self-Care

Allow more downtime and gentle self-care.
Prioritize 8+ hours of sleep and relaxing evening routines.
Try journaling, reading, or light aromatherapy.

🥗 2. Eat Supportive, Warming Foods

Focus on complex carbs, magnesium-rich, and iron-rich foods to support progesterone and reduce PMS.
✅ Great foods:
Sweet potatoes, lentils, leafy greens
Bananas, dark chocolate, pumpkin seeds
Herbal teas (chamomile, raspberry leaf)
Warm, grounding meals like soups and stews

🏋️‍♀️ 3. Switch to Gentle Workouts

Your energy is lower—opt for low-impact movement:
Pilates, yoga, stretching
Walks in nature
Restorative or yin yoga

💻 4. Wrap Up + Reflect

Ideal time for finishing projects or reviewing progress.
Your brain shifts into a more reflective, critical mode—great for planning or refining work.
Avoid high-stress tasks if possible.

💆‍♀️ 5. Support Emotional Well-being

Mood swings are more likely due to hormone shifts.
Practice mindfulness, breathwork, or gentle meditations.
Use affirmations like: “I allow myself to slow down and listen to my body.”

🌼 Bonus: Self-Care Ritual Ideas
Warm bath with Epsom salts or essential oils
Face masks + cozy loungewear
Digital detox day or journaling playlist
